## Database Schema (PostgreSQL)

### Stage 1 Tables
```sql
users         → id, email, role, tenant_id, is_active
documents     → id, tenant_id, filename, status, chunk_count, minio_key
conversations → id, tenant_id, user_id, title, created_at
messages      → id, conversation_id, role, content, citations JSONB
```

### Stage 2 Tables (add these)
```sql
settings      → key VARCHAR PK, value JSONB (hardware tier, sandbox tier)
cost_events   → id, model_id, agent_id, input_tokens, output_tokens, cost_usd, created_at
company_profiles → id, tenant_id, profile_data JSONB, created_at
```

### Stage 3 Tables (add these)
```sql
agent_runs       → id, agent_type, status, input_payload JSONB, output_payload JSONB
hitl_approvals   → id, agent_run_id, proposed_action JSONB, status, risk_level
audit_events     → id BIGSERIAL, event_type, user_id, payload JSONB (APPEND ONLY)
client_memory    → id, tenant_id, client_id, facts JSONB
prompt_versions  → id, agent_type, version, prompt_text, win_rate, created_at
projects         → id, tenant_id, client_id, title, milestones JSONB, status
invoices         → id, project_id, amount, status, sent_at
auto_approval_rules → id, action_type, threshold, never_auto BOOLEAN
```

